<html>
  <head><title>Add Z SQLRelay Database Connection</title></head>
  <body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000099" vlink="#555555" alink="#77003B">
  
    <h2>Add Z SQLRelay Database Connection</h2>
    
    <form action="manage_addZSQLRelayConnection" method="POST">
      <table cellspacing="2">
	<tr>
	  <th align="LEFT" valign="TOP">Id</th>
	  <td align="LEFT" valign="TOP">
            <input type="TEXT" name="id" size="40"
                value="SQLRelay_database_connection">
          </td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <th align="LEFT" valign="TOP"><em>Title</em></th>
	  <td align="LEFT" valign="TOP">
            <input type="TEXT" name="title" size="40"
                value="Z SQLRelay Database Connection">
          </td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <th align="LEFT" valign="TOP">
             Enter a Database Connection String
	     <a href="#1"><sup>1</sup></a></th>
	  <td align="LEFT" valign="TOP">
            <input type="TEXT" name="connection_string" size="40">
          </td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <th align="LEFT" valign="TOP">Connect immediately</th>
	  <td align="LEFT" valign="TOP">
            <input name="check" type="CHECKBOX" value="YES" CHECKED>
          </td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td></td>
	  <td><br><input type="SUBMIT" value="Add"></td>
	</tr>
      </table>
    </form>



<dt><a hname="1"><sup>1</sup></a> Connection Strings</dt>
<dd>
<p>
    The connection string used for Z SQLRleay Database Connections
    are as follows if you are using TCP sockets:
<pre>
    hostname portnumber username password
</pre>
<p>
    If you are using UNIX sockets use:
<pre>
    socketfilename username password
</pre>


</dd></dl>

  </body>
</html>
